usercssData.name: New Dev's Dark StackOverflow
usercssData.author: linoskoczek
usercssData.description: This theme is fork of Dev's Dark StackOverflow theme by Alex Saratow. He is an author of almost everything here and he is an original creator of a theme.But... as it was updated last time on 14th February 2017, I decided to fix most important things and - following the rights of the licence - publish it here, to make it easier to install, without having to make corrections on your own.Additionally, I followed Rafael Gawenda's tip to change every .so-header to .top-bar. Thank you!License stays same: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/

name: GitHub Dark
Global dark style - changes everything to DARK

usercssData.name: Global dark style - changes everything to DARK
usercssData.author: stormi
usercssData.description: Like the title says^^Applies on every website & changes as much as possible, also elements like scrollbars, buttons, cursors or the right-click menu to fit with the dark style (best result after Firefox restart). No longer possible since FF57+I'm sorry if it doesn't work good on your website but it's just not possible to make it look good everywhere. But I try my best to do so :)Easy customizeable with your own background. Just edit the style and paste the image-url.Now you can also exclude websites! Just edit the style and look at the bottom for something like "applies to - URLs with regular expression".Replace/add 'www.your.sites.here.com' with your desired ones.So it can look likehttps?://(?!(www.youtube.com|www.google.com|userstyles.org|forum.xda-developers.com)).*For some help with changing the background and excluding sites also take a look here
